  <section><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><div class="rv-q"><h3>Who is the best foundation repair company in North Texas?</h3><p>Stratum Foundation Repair is the highest-scored in our 2026 ranking (4.9★, 500+ Google reviews), with NFRA certification, a BBB A+ rating and engineered pier systems built for North Texas clay. Olshan and Structured Foundation Repairs also score strongly. The right choice depends on your soil, foundation type and project — get two or three written, engineer-backed bids before signing.</p></div><div class="rv-q"><h3>Do foundation repair companies need a license in Texas?</h3><p>No. Foundation repair is not a state-licensed trade in Texas, so there is no license number to look up. Instead, verify real credentials: BBB rating and accreditation, Foundation Repair Association or NFRA membership, whether the design and post-repair report are signed off by a licensed professional engineer, and a written transferable warranty. Be wary of any company that claims a "foundation repair license number."</p></div><div class="rv-q"><h3>How were these companies ranked?</h3><p>Each company is scored on verified Google/BBB ratings and review volume, years in business, credentials (BBB, association membership, engineer-reviewed designs, transferable warranty) and service depth. Figures come from public profiles as of June 2026, are re-checked monthly, and no company paid for placement. Where we could not verify a clean Google figure, we show a dash rather than an invented number.</p></div></section>

